text: stealing Ozma and the magic that belonged to her and to others."

text: "Are you sorry, then?" asked Dorothy, looking hard at the bird.
title: The Lost Princess of Oz

text: "I am VERY sorry," declared Ugu.  "I've been thinking over my misdeeds
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: for a long time, for doves have little else to do but think, and I'm
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: surprised that I was such a wicked man and had so little regard for the
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: rights of others.  I am now convinced that even had I succeeded in
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: making myself ruler of all Oz, I should not have been happy, for many
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: days of quiet thought have shown me that only those things one acquires
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: honestly are able to render one content."
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: "I guess that's so," said Trot.
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: "Anyhow," said Betsy, "the bad man seems truly sorry, and if he has now
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: become a good and honest man, we ought to forgive him."
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: "I fear I cannot become a good MAN again," said Ugu, "for the
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: transformation I am under will always keep me in the form of a dove.
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: But with the kind forgiveness of my former enemies, I hope to become a
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: very good dove and highly respected."
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: "Wait here till I run for my Magic Belt," said Dorothy, "and I'll
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: transform you back to your reg'lar shape in a jiffy."
title: The Lost Princess of Oz

title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: excited way.  "I only want your forgiveness.  I don't want to be a man
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: again.  As Ugu the Shoemaker I was skinny and old and unlovely.  As a
title: The Lost Princess of Oz

text: dove I am quite pretty to look at.  As a man I was ambitious and cruel,
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: while as a dove I can be content with my lot and happy in my simple
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: life.  I have learned to love the free and independent life of a bird,
title: The Lost Princess of Oz
author: Baum, L. Frank (Lyman Frank)

text: and I'd rather not change back."
title: The Lost Princess of Oz

text: "Just as you like, Ugu," said Dorothy, resuming her seat.  "Perhaps you
title: The Lost Princess of Oz

title: The Lost Princess of Oz

title: The Lost Princess of Oz

text: earnestly.
